			<p style="color:#0A50A1"><i><b>Mr.Charbel Yamouni</b> Founder</i></p>
			<p>Charbel's objective is to assist the homeless men, women and children throughout Australia. Charbel believe it is our duty to support the homeless: "If we can help one homeless person return back into the community everyone else is a bonus and we have met my objective".</p>
			<p>Charbel understands there is a strong correlation between being homeless and the increase in the unemployment rate and expectations to meet individual and family pressures. "I believe it is the responsibility of all people to help the homeless".</p>
			<p>Charbel completed his undergraduate degree at Monash University and is an experienced Project Manager, having delivered a number of national multi-million dollar projects. His skill-set will be able to assist the strategic policy and growth of Bright Sparqe to meet the organisations vision to nationally roll-out the initiative.</p>
